      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "## Motivation\r\n\r\nFixes #25227.\r\n\r\n`google/gemma-4-31B-it` failed to load with `--quantization fp8 --tp 2` when the Triton W8A8 FP8 path received an online-quantized weight scale as a row vector. The GEMM was semantically valid, but `triton_scaled_mm` only accepted the same per-output-channel scale as a column vector.\r\n\r\n## Modifications\r\n\r\n- Normalize scale tensors at the `triton_scaled_mm` boundary so scalar/1D scales become column-shaped, existing column scales are preserved, and row-vector per-output-channel weight scales shaped `(1, N)` become `(N, 1)`.\r\n- Keep the existing scale assertions after normalization so unsupported scale layouts still fail before kernel launch.\r\n- Add a regression case to the existing `test_triton_scaled_mm.py` coverage that calls `triton_scaled_mm` with `scale_b` shaped `(1, N)` and compares it with the reference output.\r\n\r\n## Root Cause\r\n\r\nThe online FP8 path quantizes non-FP8 checkpoint weights after loading:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nqweight, weight_scale = per_token_group_quant_fp8(\r\n    layer.weight, layer.weight.shape[-1]\r\n)\r\nweight_scale = weight_scale.t().contiguous()\r\nlayer.weight = Parameter(qweight.t(), requires_grad=False)\r\nlayer.weight_scale = Parameter(weight_scale, requires_grad=False)\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter that conversion:\r\n\r\n```text\r\nweight       = [K, N]\r\nweight_scale = [1, N]\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat is a valid per-output-channel scale layout. The Triton wrapper, however, only accepted scalar or column-shaped scales:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nassert scale_b.shape[1] == 1 and (scale_b.shape[0] == 1 or scale_b.shape[0] == N)\r\n```\r\n\r\nPre-fix debug capture confirmed the failing shape immediately before the assertion:\r\n\r\n```text\r\n[2026-05-14 13:46:51 TP0] triton_scaled_mm pre-fix shapes: input=(256, 5376) weight=(5376, 8192) scale_a=(256, 1) scale_b=(1, 8192) input_dtype=torch.float8_e4m3fn out_dtype=torch.bfloat16\r\n...\r\nFile \"/sgl-workspace/sglang/python/sglang/srt/layers/quantization/fp8_kernel.py\", line 2111, in triton_scaled_mm\r\n  assert scale_b.shape[1] == 1 and (scale_b.shape[0] == 1 or scale_b.shape[0] == N)\r\nAssertionError\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Accuracy Tests\r\n\r\nServer command:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nUSE_TRITON_W8A8_FP8_KERNEL=1 \\\r\npython -m sglang.launch_server \\\r\n  --model-path google/gemma-4-31B-it \\\r\n  --host 0.0.0.0 \\\r\n  --port 30000 \\\r\n  --quantization fp8 \\\r\n  --enable-metrics \\\r\n  --tp 2\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter the fix, the same path normalized row-vector weight scales and completed CUDA graph capture:\r\n\r\n```text\r\n[2026-05-14 13:23:06 TP0] triton_scaled_mm shapes: input=(32, 8192) weight=(8192, 5376) scale_a=(32, 1)->(32, 1) scale_b=(1, 5376)->(5376, 1) input_dtype=torch.float8_e4m3fn out_dtype=torch.bfloat16\r\n[2026-05-14 13:23:09 TP0] Capture cuda graph end. Time elapsed: 35.92 s. mem usage=1.78 GB. avail mem=14.77 GB.\r\n[2026-05-14 13:23:15] INFO:     Application startup complete.\r\n```\r\n\r\nA VLM request also exercised the FP8 path and returned a valid chat completion:\r\n\r\n```text\r\n[2026-05-14 13:29:03 TP1] triton_scaled_mm shapes: input=(260, 1152) weight=(1152, 5376) scale_a=(260, 1)->(260, 1) scale_b=(1, 5376)->(5376, 1) input_dtype=torch.float8_e4m3fn out_dtype=torch.bfloat16\r\n```\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"model\": \"google/gemma-4-31B-it\",\r\n  \"choices\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"message\": {\r\n        \"content\": \"A man in a yellow shirt is ironing a blue garment on an ironing board set up on the back of a yellow taxi in a city street.\"\r\n      },\r\n      \"finish_reason\": \"stop\"\r\n    }\r\n  ],\r\n  \"usage\": {\r\n    \"prompt_tokens\": 282,\r\n    \"completion_tokens\": 30,\r\n    \"total_tokens\": 312\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<!-- pr-states:start -->\n---\n### CI States\n\nLatest PR Test (Base): <!-- slot:pr-test:start -->:white_check_mark: [Run #26094843578](https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/actions/runs/26094843578)<!-- slot:pr-test:end -->\nLatest PR Test (Extra): <!-- slot:pr-test-extra:start -->:warning: **Not enabled** -- add `run-ci-extra` label to opt in.<!-- slot:pr-test-extra:end -->\n<!-- pr-states:end -->",
